tents  education and early life  career and research  awards and honors  personal life  references education and early lifeedit walter gilbert was born in boston massachusetts on march   the son of emma cohen a child psychologist and richard v gilbert an economist he was educated at the sidwell friends school and attended harvard university for undergraduate and graduate studies earning a baccalaureate in chemistry and physics in  and a masters degree in physics in  he studied for his doctorate at the university of cambridge where he earned a phd in physics supervised by the nobel laureate abdus salam in  career and researchedit gilbert returned to harvard in  and was appointed assistant professor of physics in  gilberts wife celia had begun working for james watson and this led to gilbert becoming interested in problems in molecular biology watson and gilbert would run their laboratory jointly through most of the s until watson left for cold spring harbor laboratory in  he was promoted to associate professor of biophysics and promoted again in  to professor of biochemistry he is a cofounder of the biotech startup companies biogen and myriad genetics and was the first chairman on their respective boards of directors gilbert left his position at harvard to run biogen as ceo but was later asked to resign by the companys board of directors he is also a member of the board of scientific governors at the scripps research institute gilbert has served as the chairman of the harvard society of fellows in  gilbert cofounded paratek pharmaceuticals inc along with dr stuart b levy gilbert served as chairman until  gilbert was an early proponent of sequencing the human genome at a march  meeting in santa fe new mexico he proclaimed the total human sequence is the grail of human genetics in  he proposed starting a company called genome corporation to sequence the genome and sell access to the information in an opinion piece in nature in  he envisioned completion of the human genome sequence transforming biology into a field in which computer databases would be as essential as laboratory reagents gilbert returned to harvard in  gilbert was an outspoken critic of david baltimore in the handling of the scientific fraud accusations against thereza imanishikari gilbert also joined the early controversy over the cause of aids though he later stated he was satisfied with the evidence that disease is caused by hivcitation needed in  gilberts phd student in physics gerald guralnik extended gilberts work on massless particles guralniks work on is widely recognized as an important thread in the discovery of the higgs boson with his phd student benno müllerhill gilbert was the first to purify the lac repressor just beating out mark ptashne for purifying the first gene regulatory protein together with allan maxam gilbert developed a new dna sequencing method using chemical methods developed by andrei mirzabekov his approach to the first synthesis of insulin via recombinant dna lost out to genentechs approach which used genes built up from the nucleotides rather than from natural sources gilberts effort was hampered by a temporary moratorium on recombinant dna work in cambridge massachusetts forcing his group to move their work to an english biological weapons site gilbert first proposed the existence of introns and exons and explained the evolution of introns in a seminal  news and views paper published in nature in  gilbert proposed the rna world hypothesis for the origin of life based on a concept first proposed by carl woese in  awards and honorsedit walter gilbert portrait via the national library of medicine in  gilbert was awarded harvards ledlie prize in  he was named american cancer society professor of molecular biology in  gilbert was awarded the louisa gross horwitz prize from columbia university together with frederick sanger that year he was also awarded the gairdner prize and the albert lasker award for basic medical research gilbert was awarded the  nobel prize in chemistry shared with frederick sanger and paul berg gilbert and sanger were recognized for their pioneering work in devising methods for determining the sequence of nucleotides in a nucleic acid gilbert has also been honored by the national academy of sciences us steel foundation award  massachusetts general hospital warren triennial prize citation needed the new york academy of sciences louis and bert freedman foundation award  the academie des sciences of france prix charlesleopold mayer award  gilbert was elected a foreign member of the royal society formemrs in  in  he received the biotechnology heritage award personal lifeedit gilbert married celia stone in  and has two children after retiring from harvard in  gilbert has launched an artistic career centered on digital photography referencesedit  church g gilbert w  genomic sequencing proceedings of the national academy of sciences of the united states of america   – bibcodepnasc pmc   pmid  doipnas   a b c d nobel prize autobiography walter gilbert  a b c d e f g h i j k l shampo ma kyle ra may  walter gilbert nobel prize for chemistry mayo clin proc    pmid  doi   walter gilberts publications indexed by the scopus bibliographic database a service provided by elsevier subscription required  httpwwwchilitorgpublishedpapersschwartzbergadvocatepdf  gilbert walter  on generalised dispersion relations and mesonnucleon scattering phd thesis university of cambridge oclc    watson james d  genes girls and gamow   a b kanigel robert december   the genome project the new york times magazine   httpsparatekpharmacomaboutfoundersdrgilbert  gilbert walter  towards a paradigm shift in biology nature    bibcodenaturg doia   a b johnson carolyn y march   a physicist biologist nobel laureate ceo and now artist the boston globe   kolata gina june   inquiry lacking due process the new york times books   cohen jon december   the duesberg phenomenon pdf science  – bibcodescic pmid  doiscience   close fr