uated with a degree in physics in  he then went on to attend cambridge university trinity college in england aided by a national science foundation fellowship at cambridge his thesis advisor was future nobel laureate abdus salam and in  he graduated with a phd in mathematics after graduation he returned to the united states and married celia stone a poet he met while attending sidwell friends school in  gilbert joined the faculty at harvard as a lecturer in physics and in  he was appointed assistant professor of physics in the early s he became interested in messenger rna and worked with james d watson on experiments to isolate the nucleic acid from this point on gilbert’s scientific career would be primarily focused on molecular biology his first paper on messenger rna appeared in nature in  while his last paper on physics would be published in  in  he was appointed associate professor of biophysics and in  he was promoted to professor of biophysics beginning in the mids he began investigating why different cells produce different proteins even though they have identical dna and with benno müllerhill he isolated the lac repressor gene in escherichia coli which prevented the production of certain enzymes except when lactose is present in the cell this confirmed an earlier theory proposed by jacques monod and françois jacob that repressor genes regulate the process of protein synthesis in the cell he then went on to develop a pioneering method for determining the sequence of nucleotides in a nucleic acid frederick sanger independently developed the same method for this work he was awarded the  louisa gross horwitz prize from columbia university with sanger the  albert lasker basic medical research award with sanger and roger wolcott sperry and finally the  nobel prize in chemistry with sanger and paul berg in  he cofounded with other prominent biologists and businessmen biogen one of the earliest biotechnology companies he left harvard to run the company in  in  he resigned as chairman and ceo of biogen and returned to harvard to conduct research in  he was appointed carl m loeb university professor at the university in  he founded the biotechnology company myriad genetics and would go to serve on the advisory board of numerous other biotech firms he is married to celia stone and has two children scope and content the walter gilbert collection at cshl library and archives is composed of material accrued by gilbert as a student sidwell friends school harvard university cambridge university professor harvard university and as a pioneering entrepreneur in the field of biotechnology biogen the collection includes course notebooks lecture notes and teaching files scientific papers correspondence photographs memorabilia clippings and material related to receiving the nobel prize archive links institutional archivesgenentech centerrare booksoral historyguide to the hgp personal collections walter gilbert finding aid  ead archive quick links archives repositoryjames d watson collectionsydney brenner collectiondigital collectionscshl symposiaoral historycshl historyarchive news  blogmemory board contact the archives support the archives availability of material for specific information on the availability of materials or to arrange an appointment to use the archives please contact  or this email address is being protected from spambots you need javascript enabled to view it please consult our permissions  copyright policies for any materials you wish to use copyright   cold spring harbor laboratory  library  archives all rights reserved joomla is free software released under the gnu general public license myriad genetics inc mygn director gilbert walter phds insider stock buys and sells home homepage membership levels membership data coverage complete stock list founders message the book free trial screeners value screens allinone screener industry overview ben graham netnet undervalued predictable buffettmunger screener magic formula g